<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144648>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7–8. Scydmaenus (Choleropsis) beechmonti Franz, male. Head, pronotum and elytral base in dorsal view (7); head and prothorax in ventral view (8). Abbreviations: abp, antebasal pits; bst, basistipes; bstr, basisternal region of prosternum; gen, gena; gp, gular plate; hr, hypomeral ridge; hyr, hypostomal ridge; lp, labial palp; md, mandible; mn, mentum; mst, mediostipes; mxp, maxillary palp; occ, occipital constriction; plb, prelabium; pmc, posterior marginal carina; ppf, palpifer; prcc, procoxal cavity; ptp, posterior tentorial pit; smn, submentum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144648/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144650>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9–11. Scydmaenus (Choleropsis) beechmonti Franz, male. Distal region of right antenna in dorsal (9) and outer lateral (10) views; pterothorax and abdomen in ventral view (11). Abbreviations: aest3, metanepisternum; amvp, anterior metaventral process; a6‒11, antennomere 6‒11; mscc, mesocoxal cavity; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; pcr, procoxal rest; prp, prepectus; pyg, pygidium; sIII‒VIII, sternite III‒VIII." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144650/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144652>
    dc:description "FIGURES 12–14. Scydmaenus (Choleropsis) beechmonti Franz, male. Right protarsus in lateral view (12), distal region of mesotibia and proximal region of mesotarsus in lateral view (13); distal region of mesotibia and mesotarsus in lateral view (14). Abbreviations: t1‒5, tarsomere 1‒5." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144652/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144654>
    dc:description "FIGURES 15–19. Scydmaenus (Choleropsis) beechmonti Franz, male. Dorsal habitus (15); aedeagus in dorsal (16, 18) and lateral (17, 19) views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144664>
    dc:description "FIGURES 41–45. Scydmaenus (Choleropsis) curviclavatus sp. n., male. Dorsal habitus (41); aedeagus in dorsal (42, 44) and lateral (43, 45) views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144664/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144668>
    dc:description "FIGURES 51–57. Antennae of Choleropsis in dorsal view, males (51, 53–57) and female (52). Scydmaenus beechmonti Franz (51–52); S. geniculatus (King) (53); S. kurandae Franz (54); S. princeps (King) (55); S. curviclavatus sp. n. (56); S. kroombitanus sp. n. (57)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144668/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144670>
    dc:description "FIGURES 58–69. Antennal clubs of Choleropsis in dorsal (58, 60, 62, 64, 66, 68) and outer lateral (59, 61, 63, 65, 67, 69) views, males. Scydmaenus beechmonti Franz (58–59); S. geniculatus (King) (60–61); S. kurandae Franz (62–63); S. princeps (King) (64–65); S. curviclavatus sp. n. (66–67); S. kroombitanus sp. n. (68–69)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144670/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144672>
    dc:description "FIGURES 70–75. Pterothorax of Choleropsis in ventral views, males. Scydmaenus beechmonti Franz (70); S. geniculatus (King) (71); S. kurandae Franz (72); S. princeps (King) (73); S. curviclavatus sp. n. (74); S. kroombitanus sp. n. (75)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144672/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144723>
    dc:description "FIGURES 189–205. Historical labels of primary type specimens. Lectotype of Heterognathus gracilis King (189); holotype of Scydmaenus beechmonti Franz (190); lectotype of Heterognathus geniculatus King (191); holotype of Scydmaenus kurandae Franz (192); lectotype of Heterognathus princeps King (193); holotype of Scydmaenus marwillumbali Franz [© Lisha Jasper, (BM)] (194); lectotype of Heterognathus carinatus King (195); holotype of Scydmaenus formicarum Franz (196); holotype of Scydmaenus australiensis Franz (197); lectotype of Heterognathus myrmecophilus Lea (198); holotype of Scydmaenus inflatitibia Franz (199); holotype of Scydmaenus clarkianus Franz (200); lectotype of Scydmaenus optatus Sharp (201); holotype of Scydmaenus scotti Franz (202); lectotype of Scydmaenus swanensis Franz (203); holotype of Scydmaenus brachyponerophilus sp. n. (204); syntype of Heterognathus armitagei King [© Natalie Tees (AMS)] (205)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144723/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

